The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Zurich, Jan. 4: Swiss drug maker Novartis wants to take over eye care firm Alcon for $39.3 billion, including Nestles majority stake, to help it diversify away from prescription drugs. Novartis is exercising an option to buy a 52 per cent stake in Alcon from Nestle for $28.1 billion, boosting its holding to 77 per cent after it bought an initial 25 per cent stake in Alcon from the food group in 2008.                            
	 London, Jan. 4: Prices of copper rose 2 per cent to a 16-month high today, building on gains of about 140 per cent last year, because of strikes in top producer Chile and as more investors piled into the metal. Benchmark copper traded at $7,504 a tonne against $7,375 on Thursday on the London Metal Exchange.                             
	 London, Jan. 4: Oil price surged above $81 today on expectations of higher energy demand in the northern hemisphere for the cold weather, and after Russia cut supplies to Belarus, traders said.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 4: Five major federations of port and dock workers, who had threatened an indefinite strike from today, called off the agitation after the government agreed to their wage revision demand.
                                                                                                                          
